    6: "Mars in the 6th house tends toward intense, methodical work energy oriented toward daily efficiency. The will mobilizes in service, solving concrete problems, and tending to health. This placement invites one to channel combativeness into the continuous improvement of systems and well-being. Strength expresses itself fully when work energy is supported by attentive care of the body.",
    7: "Mars in the 7th house invites an action energy that unfolds primarily within relationships and partnerships. The will seeks the other as a sparring partner, a mirror of its own strength. This placement tends toward passionate and sometimes conflictual relationships that serve as grounds for growth. Relational power is fulfilled when confrontation becomes a dance of mutual growth.",
    8: "Mars in the 8th house deploys a transformative energy of magnetic intensity, plunging into the depths of existence. The will mobilizes in crises, situations of power, and taboo territories. This placement invites one to use this regenerative power to traverse ordeals and emerge stronger. Strength is fulfilled when the survival instinct transmutes into the capacity to be reborn.",
    9: "Mars in the 9th house tends toward an energy of exploration, intellectual conquest, and defense of convictions. The will deploys itself in travel, passionate teaching, and fighting for one's beliefs. This placement invites one to channel philosophical ardor into quests that elevate consciousness. Power is fulfilled when missionary zeal is tinged with tolerance and openness.",
    10: "Mars in the 10th house invites an ambitious and determined energy aiming for the heights of professional achievement. The will mobilizes to conquer a position of power and leave a mark on the world. This placement tends toward strong, dynamic, and sometimes controversial leadership. Strength is fulfilled when ambition serves a mission that transcends the ego.",
    11: "Mars in the 11th house deploys its energy in collective projects, social causes, and the defense of ideals. The will mobilizes to change the world, unite groups, and champion causes greater than the individual. This placement invites one to channel combativeness into actions of solidarity and innovation. Power is fulfilled when revolutionary energy builds as much as it disrupts.",
    12: "Mars in the 12th house tends toward an inner, sometimes underground action energy that operates in the invisible. The will manifests in solitude, secret work, and the struggle against inner adversaries. This placement invites one to transform the frustration of energy that finds no outlet into spiritual force. Power reveals itself when invisible action in service of others becomes the highest form of courage.",
